{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a3f7c2d1-58e4-4b9a-bc31-7e6d05f1a820",
    "name": "FinTrackPro API — E2E",
    "description": "CI-gating E2E collection for FinTrackPro. Runs full lifecycle flows against a real API process with a real Keycloak-issued JWT.\n\nCovers critical paths: Auth, resource CRUD flows, authorization ownership guards, and third-party market contracts (CoinGecko).\n\nValidation / negative-input tests live in `FinTrackPro.dev.postman_collection.json`.\n\n**Setup:**\n1. Import `FinTrackPro.postman_environment.json`\n2. Local test credentials are prefilled for the committed Keycloak test realm\n3. `bearerToken` is minted by the dedicated \"Mint bearerToken\" request in the Auth folder (second item), which POSTs directly to Keycloak so the token is synchronously available before the Trades folder starts\n\n**Newman (CI/local):**\n```bash\nbash scripts/api-e2e-local.sh\n\n# Or directly:\nnewman run FinTrackPro.e2e.postman_collection.json \\\n  -e FinTrackPro.postman_environment.json \\\n  --env-var \"baseUrl=http://localhost:5018\" \\\n  --env-var \"keycloakUrl=http://localhost:8080\" \\\n  --env-var \"testUsername=admin@fintrackpro.dev\" \\\n  --env-var \"testPassword=Admin1234!\" \\\n  --env-var \"testUsername2=user2@fintrackpro.dev\" \\\n  --env-var \"testPassword2=User2Pass!\" \\\n  --bail -r cli,junit --reporter-junit-export test-results/newman.xml\n```",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{bearerToken}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "exec": [
          "// Always reset testMonth at run start so a stale value from a previous run or",
          "// --env-export file never causes false collisions.",
          "const now = new Date();",
          "const month = now.getFullYear() + '-' + String(now.getMonth() + 1).padStart(2, '0');",
          "pm.environment.set('testMonth', month);"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "No token → GET /api/transactions → 401",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/transactions"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Returns 401 when no token provided', () => {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(401);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Mint bearerToken → POST Keycloak /token → 200",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                { "key": "grant_type", "value": "password",          "type": "text" },
                { "key": "client_id",  "value": "fintrackpro-e2e",   "type": "text" },
                { "key": "username",   "value": "{{testUsername}}",  "type": "text" },
                { "key": "password",   "value": "{{testPassword}}",  "type": "text" }
              ]
            },
            "url": "{{keycloakUrl}}/realms/fintrackpro/protocol/openid-connect/token"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Keycloak returns 200 and access_token present', () => {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(body).to.have.property('access_token');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (!body.access_token) {",
                  "    throw new Error('Token mint failed: ' + JSON.stringify(body));",
                  "}",
                  "pm.environment.set('bearerToken', body.access_token);",
                  "pm.environment.set('_tokenExpiry',",
                  "    String(Date.now() + (body.expires_in - 30) * 1000));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Trades — Full lifecycle",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /api/trades → 201, capture tradeId",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/trades",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"symbol\": \"BTCUSDT\",\n  \"direction\": \"Long\",\n  \"entryPrice\": 60000.0,\n  \"exitPrice\": 65000.0,\n  \"positionSize\": 0.1,\n  \"fees\": 5.0,\n  \"notes\": \"Breakout trade\",\n  \"currency\": \"USD\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.test('Returns a GUID and captures tradeId', () => {",
                  "  const id = pm.response.text().replace(/\"/g, '');",
                  "  pm.expect(id).to.match(/^[0-9a-f-]{36}$/i);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('tradeId', id);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /api/trades → 200, trade in list, result computed correctly",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/trades"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Returns array with the created trade', () => {",
                  "  const trades = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(trades).to.be.an('array');",
                  "  const tradeId = pm.environment.get('tradeId');",
                  "  const trade = trades.find(t => t.id === tradeId);",
                  "  pm.expect(trade, 'created trade present in list').to.exist;",
                  "  pm.expect(trade).to.have.property('id');",
                  "  pm.expect(trade).to.have.property('symbol');",
                  "  pm.expect(trade).to.have.property('direction');",
                  "  pm.expect(trade).to.have.property('result');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "PUT /api/trades/{{tradeId}} → 200, updated fields + re-computed result",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/trades/{{tradeId}}",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"symbol\": \"BTCUSDT\",\n  \"direction\": \"Long\",\n  \"entryPrice\": 60000,\n  \"exitPrice\": 67000,\n  \"positionSize\": 0.1,\n  \"fees\": 5,\n  \"notes\": \"Updated target hit\\nTook partial profits\",\n  \"currency\": \"USD\",\n  \"status\": \"Closed\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Returns updated TradeDto with re-computed result', () => {",
                  "  const trade = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(trade).to.have.property('id');",
                  "  pm.expect(trade).to.have.property('symbol');",
                  "  pm.expect(trade).to.have.property('direction');",
                  "  pm.expect(trade).to.have.property('result');",
                  "  pm.expect(trade.exitPrice).to.eql(67000.0);",
                  "  pm.expect(trade.notes).to.include('Updated target hit');",
                  "  // result = (67000 - 60000) * 0.1 - 5 = 695",
                  "  pm.expect(trade.result).to.be.closeTo(695, 1);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "DELETE /api/trades/{{tradeId}} → 204",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/trades/{{tradeId}}"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 204', () => pm.response.to.have.status(204));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /api/trades → 200, trade no longer in list",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/trades"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Deleted trade is no longer in list', () => {",
                  "  const trades = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(trades).to.be.an('array');",
                  "  const tradeId = pm.environment.get('tradeId');",
                  "  const found = trades.some(t => t.id === tradeId);",
                  "  pm.expect(found, 'deleted trade should not be present').to.be.false;",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Budgets + Transactions — Spending flow",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /api/budgets → 201, capture budgetId",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/budgets",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"category\": \"Food\",\n  \"limitAmount\": 500.00,\n  \"month\": \"{{testMonth}}\",\n  \"currency\": \"USD\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// Delete any stale Food budget left from a previous failed run to prevent 409.",
                  "const testMonth = pm.environment.get('testMonth');",
                  "const token = pm.environment.get('bearerToken');",
                  "const baseUrl = pm.environment.get('baseUrl');",
                  "",
                  "pm.sendRequest({",
                  "    url: `${baseUrl}/api/budgets/${testMonth}`,",
                  "    method: 'GET',",
                  "    header: [{ key: 'Authorization', value: `Bearer ${token}` }]",
                  "}, (err, res) => {",
                  "    if (!err && res.code === 200) {",
                  "        const food = res.json().find(b => b.category === 'Food');",
                  "        if (food) {",
                  "            pm.sendRequest({",
                  "                url: `${baseUrl}/api/budgets/${food.id}`,",
                  "                method: 'DELETE',",
                  "                header: [{ key: 'Authorization', value: `Bearer ${token}` }]",
                  "            }, () => {});",
                  "        }",
                  "    }",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.test('Returns a GUID and captures budgetId', () => {",
                  "  const id = pm.response.text().replace(/\"/g, '');",
                  "  pm.expect(id).to.match(/^[0-9a-f-]{36}$/i);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('budgetId', id);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /api/transaction-categories → 200, capture foodCategoryId",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/transaction-categories?type=Expense"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Finds food_beverage category and captures foodCategoryId', () => {",
                  "  const categories = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(categories).to.be.an('array');",
                  "  const food = categories.find(c => c.slug === 'food_beverage');",
                  "  pm.expect(food, 'food_beverage category exists').to.exist;",
                  "  pm.environment.set('foodCategoryId', food.id);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /api/transactions → 201, capture transactionId",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/transactions",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"type\": \"Expense\",\n  \"amount\": 120.50,\n  \"categoryId\": \"{{foodCategoryId}}\",\n  \"note\": \"Grocery run\",\n  \"budgetMonth\": \"{{testMonth}}\",\n  \"currency\": \"USD\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.test('Returns a GUID and captures transactionId', () => {",
                  "  const id = pm.response.text().replace(/\"/g, '');",
                  "  pm.expect(id).to.match(/^[0-9a-f-]{36}$/i);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('transactionId', id);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /api/transactions?month={{testMonth}} → 200, tx present with correct fields",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/transactions?month={{testMonth}}"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Returns array containing the created transaction', () => {",
                  "  const txs = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(txs).to.be.an('array');",
                  "  const txId = pm.environment.get('transactionId');",
                  "  const tx = txs.find(t => t.id === txId);",
                  "  pm.expect(tx, 'created transaction present').to.exist;",
                  "  pm.expect(tx).to.have.property('id');",
                  "  pm.expect(tx.amount).to.be.closeTo(120.50, 0.01);",
                  "  pm.expect(tx.category).to.be.a('string').and.not.equal('');",
                  "  pm.expect(tx.categoryId).to.eql(pm.environment.get('foodCategoryId'));",
                  "  pm.expect(tx).to.have.property('budgetMonth');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "PATCH /api/transactions/{{transactionId}} → 204, verify fields updated",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/transactions/{{transactionId}}",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"type\": \"Expense\",\n  \"amount\": 95.00,\n  \"currency\": \"USD\",\n  \"category\": \"food_beverage\",\n  \"note\": \"Updated grocery run\",\n  \"categoryId\": \"{{foodCategoryId}}\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 204', () => pm.response.to.have.status(204));",
                  "",
                  "// Verify the update took effect by fetching the transaction list",
                  "const token = pm.environment.get('bearerToken');",
                  "const baseUrl = pm.environment.get('baseUrl');",
                  "const txId = pm.environment.get('transactionId');",
                  "const testMonth = pm.environment.get('testMonth');",
                  "pm.sendRequest({",
                  "    url: `${baseUrl}/api/transactions?month=${testMonth}`,",
                  "    method: 'GET',",
                  "    header: [{ key: 'Authorization', value: `Bearer ${token}` }]",
                  "}, (err, res) => {",
                  "    pm.test('Updated transaction reflects new amount', () => {",
                  "        const txs = res.json();",
                  "        const tx = txs.find(t => t.id === txId);",
                  "        pm.expect(tx, 'transaction still present after update').to.exist;",
                  "        pm.expect(tx.amount).to.be.closeTo(95.00, 0.01);",
                  "        pm.expect(tx.note).to.eql('Updated grocery run');",
                  "    });",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "PATCH /api/budgets/{{budgetId}} → 204",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/budgets/{{budgetId}}",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"limitAmount\": 750.00\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
